  "read": {
    "bulk_latency": "At both EP4 and EP8 owner-rank shapes, the local MoE VJP wall is still dominated by GEMM-family work: forward recompute is about 2.5-2.7 ms, wgrad is about 2.37-2.39 ms, and xgrad plus scatter/reduce is about 1.65 ms. The fused SwiGLU kernels are now small, roughly 0.10-0.14 ms each.",
    "why_ep8_is_better_than_ep4": "EP8 has fewer local experts and a larger mean M per local expert, so padding drops from 1.149x to 1.057x. That makes the owner-rank local VJP slightly better even though the assignment count is similar.",
    "recompute_tax": "Saving the true training intermediates gate/up/hidden saves about 1.17-1.26 ms per owner-rank VJP; saving compact output as well saves about 1.58-1.88 ms. The public AITER-style stage1-hidden-only contract saves almost nothing because backward still needs gate and up to form SwiGLU derivatives.",
    "decision": "Do not chase dispatch/combine-only or Primus-Turbo grouped-GEMM-only swaps for this MoE backward wall. The next useful branches are a training-aware fused MoE backward contract that either saves gate/up/hidden/out_compact or recomputes them inside one fused pipeline, plus a better grouped wgrad/xgrad GEMM backend for the owner-rank EP shape."
  },
